Got it. Here's the full roadmap:

───

Part 1 — Skills to Install

Run these via clawhub CLI (some may need retry if rate limited):

clawhub install abm-schema-markup
clawhub install abm-competitor-alternatives

Skills you'll have:

• abm-programmatic-seo ✅ (already installed)
• abm-seo-audit ✅ (already installed)
• abm-schema-markup ⏳ (install it)
• abm-competitor-alternatives ⏳ (install it)

───

Part 2 — Infrastructure

src/app/sitemap.js — Next.js 15+ native sitemap (no package needed). Returns all static + dynamic routes. Should include: landing, pricing, blog, personas, comparisons, integrations, glossary.

src/app/robots.txt — Allow all, point to sitemap.

src/app/(public)/og/route.jsx — Dynamic OG image generation via next/og. One route, query params for title/service/type.

───

Part 3 — Data Layer

Create src/data/ with:

• services.js — trades you serve (plumber, HVAC, handyman, electrician, etc.)
• personas.js — each persona: slug, title, meta description, pain points, objections, testimonials, CTAs
• comparisons.js — each comparison: slug, who you're vs, pros/cons, verdict
• integrations.js — each integration: slug, tool name, description, use cases
• blog-posts.js — post metadata: slug, title, description, date, author, category, tags

Each file exports an array. This is your programmatic generation engine.

───

Part 4 — Page Templates to Build

Blog — /blog listing + /blog/[slug] detail. Use generateStaticParams + generateMetadata.

Personas — /for/[persona] with template that renders persona-specific copy, pain points, features, social proof. Target: plumbers, HVAC contractors, handymen, electricians.

Comparisons — /compare/[comparison] with template. Start with: voicemail vs AI receptionist, ringcentral vs voco, jobber vs manual scheduling.

Integrations — /integrations/[tool] with template. Start with: jobber, housecall-pro, stripe, google-calendar.

Glossary — /glossary/[term] with template. FAQ schema markup here is a must.

───

Part 5 — Schema Markup Component

Build src/components/SchemaMarkup.jsx that accepts type + data, renders <script type="application/ld+json">. Types to implement:

• LocalBusiness — for landing page
• FAQPage — for glossary + blog posts
• WebPage — base for all pages
• SoftwareApplication — for integrations pages

───

Part 6 — Metadata Per Page Type

Every dynamic page needs generateMetadata() returning:

• title — template: {PageName} | Voco
• description — from data layer
• openGraph — image from /og/route?title=...
• alternates — canonical URL
• robots — index, follow for public pages

───

Part 7 — Internal Linking

Every page should link to:

• Related pages of same type (blog → blog, integration → integration)
• Hub page (persona pages → /for, glossary → /glossary)
• Relevant CTAs to signup/trial

No orphan pages. Every programmatic page reachable from a hub.

───

Execution Order

1. Install remaining skills
2. sitemap.js + robots.txt (foundation)
3. OG image route (used everywhere)
4. Data layer files (your content config)
5. Schema markup component
6. Blog scaffold → write 2-3 posts
7. Personas pages (your top-of-funnel B2B play)
8. Comparisons pages (high commercial intent)
9. Integrations pages (warm leads from existing tool users)
10. Glossary pages (bottom funnel + authority)
11. Audit with abm-seo-audit

